Actions on Template

To review the templates use actions menu.

Edit

 

To change the content of the template use Edit action.

Activate Template

 

To activate template and make it available in the system use Activate Template button.

Deactivate Template

 

To deactivate template use Deactivate Template button. The template is no more available in the template list while creating an object.

Set as primary

 

To make a template primary use Set as Primary action. The template will be used as default template while creating a new system object.

Manage rules

 

To set a restrictions based on rules when template to be visible click on Manage rules action. 

Update existing objects

 

To update all existing templates with the last active template use Update existing objects action. All already created items that use that template will be updated based on the following rules:

  • All locked tabs in the selected instance are replaced with the respective locked tabs from the new template.

  •  If there are new tabs in the template, that do not exist in the existing instances, then these tabs are added in instances.
  •  If there are locked tabs in the template that are unlocked in the instances and vice versa then these tabs are also replaced in existing instances.
  • All tabs in the existing instances that are created by the users are not touched, and they remain as created by the user.
  • If there is a tab deleted from the new template, then the tab is deleted also from the instances. (Only the user created tabs remain).

Clone

 

To clone a template use Clone action. This can help you when creating a new template, not to start from a blank one, but just to update already created one.

Lock

 

To lock a template for editing by other users use Lock template action.

Unlock

 

To unlock a template that is locked for editing use Unlock action
